Gauteng Premier David Makhura paid his last tribute to Phillip Kgosana on behalf of the provincial and national government. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng Premier David Makhura has described the late Pan Africanist Congress (PAC) struggle stalwart Phillip Kgosana as a great patriot and national hero who belongs to a special generation of South Africans.His funeral service is currently underway in Pretoria.Kgosana died at the age of 80 after a short illness.In 1960, he led more than 30,000 anti-pass law protesters.Makhura paid his last tribute to Kgosana on behalf of the provincial and national government.&quot;Ntate Kgosana s name belongs to the role call of honour, the heroes of our struggle who suffered sacrificed enormously for justice and freedom in our land.&quot;President Jacob Zuma has declared a special provincial funeral for the veteran.